org.jcvi.jillion.trace.sff

Class SffFileDataStoreBuilder

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jcvi.jillion.trace.sff.SffFileDataStoreBuilder

  • public class SffFileDataStoreBuilder
extends Object
    SffFileDataStoreBuilder is a Builder that can create new instances of SffFileDataStores using data from a given input sff file.

    dkatzel

    • Method Detail

      • filter

        public SffFileDataStoreBuilder filter(DataStoreFilter filter)
        Only include the FastqRecords which pass the given DataStoreFilter. If a filter is not given to this builder, then all records in the sff file will be included in the built SffFileDataStore.
        Parameters:
        filter - a DataStoreFilter instance that can be used to filter out specified flowgram records; can not be null.
        Returns:
        this.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if filter is null.

      • hint

        public SffFileDataStoreBuilder hint(DataStoreProviderHint hint)
        Provide a DataStoreProviderHint to this builder to let it know the implementation preferences of the client. If no hint is given, then this builder will try to store all the flowgram records in memory which may cause an Exception if there isn't enough memory. The DataStoreProviderHint is just a guideline and may be ignored by this builder when determining which SffFileDataStore implementation to chose to build in build().
        Parameters:
        hint - an instance of DataStoreProviderHint; can not be null.
        Returns:
        this
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if hint is null.
        See Also:
        DataStoreProviderHint

      • build

        public SffFileDataStore build()
                       throws IOException
        Parse the given sff file and return a new instance of a SffFileDataStore using all the input parameters given so far. If not all optional parameters are set then default values will be used:
        • If no DataStoreFilter has been specified by filter(DataStoreFilter), then all SffFlowgrams will be included in this SffFileDataStore.
        • If no DataStoreProviderHint has been specified by hint(DataStoreProviderHint), then this builder will try to store all the SffFlowgrams that meet the DataStoreFilter requirements in memory. This may cause out of memory errors if there is not enough memory available.
        Returns:
        a new SffFileDataStore instance; never null.
        Throws:
        IOException - if there is a problem parsing the sff file.
        See Also:
        hint(DataStoreProviderHint)
